      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the non-cannulated 7.5 mm screw construct model. Stiffness QoI varied by 1.4% between medium and fine meshes; yield force by 1.8%. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) computed per Roache 1998: GCI < 3.2% for all three QoIs. Final mesh: ~420,000 elements, predominantly hex-dominant with quadratic formulation at screw-rod interface."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals below 1e-6 for all load steps; Newton-Raphson convergence achieved within 15 iterations per step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear static analyses used sparse direct solver with force and displacement convergence criteria of 1e-6. All 11 load cases converged within 12 iterations per load step. No solver warnings or divergence events recorded in solution logs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent model review by second analyst; documented simulation plan reviewed prior to execution.",
      "rationale": "A simulation plan document was prepared and reviewed by an independent analyst before model execution. Boundary condition application, material assignment, and contact definition were independently verified against the simulation plan. No discrepancies identified. Achieved level meets required level."
