      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear elastic titanium alloy material model with frictional contact at screw-rod interface justified by literature and sensitivity analysis; geometric nonlinearity included.",
      "rationale": "Ti-6Al-4V linear elastic material (E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) consistent with ASTM F136 coupon data. Frictional contact (mu=0.3) at screw-rod interface validated against published tribology data. Geometric nonlinearity (large displacement) activated given expected deflections up to 40 mm. Sensitivity analysis confirmed model form uncertainty contributes <5% to total QoI uncertainty budget."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric dimensions sourced from ASTM F136 certificates and CMM measurements of test articles; uncertainty propagated through model.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus and yield strength from material certificates for the same lot used in bench testing. Screw and rod dimensions from CMM measurements of three representative test articles (mean ± 1 SD reported). Probabilistic sensitivity analysis (Latin hypercube, N=500) shows combined input uncertainty contributes ±4.1% to stiffness QoI, within the 10% acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lot; dimensional inspection confirms geometric conformance to nominal CAD.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs assembled per ASTM F1717 from a single production lot. CMM inspection of all 11 constructs confirmed dimensions within ±0.05 mm of nominal CAD geometry. Inter-construct variability in stiffness: CV=3.2%, consistent with expected manufacturing tolerances."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span at least two load levels or two construct configurations to bound the COU loading envelope.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at one load rate (5 mm/min). While two independent laboratories conducted testing (inter-lab reproducibility confirmed), only one test condition (load configuration and rate) was evaluated. This limits the ability to bound the full COU loading envelope. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3); this gap is acknowledged and accepted given that the COU is specifically defined for the F1717 compression-bending configuration only."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate ASTM F1717 fixture geometry and applied displacement to within measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 fixture geometry (block spacing 100 mm, offset 35 mm) reproduced in FEA to within 0.1 mm based on fixture CMM data. Applied displacement ramp in FEA matches test machine crosshead displacement profile. Constraint conditions (fixed inferior block, displacement-controlled superior block) confirmed equivalent between model and test setup by independent review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation metric E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10% for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm).",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA 187 N/mm vs. experimental mean 192 N/mm (2.6% difference; E/uval=0.81). Yield force: FEA 412 N vs. experimental mean 421 N (2.1% difference; E/uval=0.74). Force at 40 mm: FEA 638 N vs. experimental mean 651 N (2.0% difference; E/uval=0.69). All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria. Validation metric computed per ASME V&V 40 Section 5.4 using combined experimental and simulation uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are the same metrics used in the regulatory submission design verification testing.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are explicitly required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw design verification under ASTM F1717. They directly characterize construct mechanical performance relevant to the clinical failure modes (permanent deformation, fatigue initiation). QoIs in the validation study are identical to those in the design verification protocol, confirming high relevance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation constructs are the same device, same material lot, same assembly procedure, and same test standard as the COU.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the identical non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw device from the same production lot, assembled per the same surgical technique guide, and tested per ASTM F1717 — the same standard and configuration as the COU. No interpolation or extrapolation from surrogate geometries was required. Validation activity relevance to COU is assessed as high."
    }
